</taxonomicName>
are seen by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7A67F993FF4FF00E" author="Zhu, Y. - Q. &amp; Buck, W. R. &amp; Wang, Y. - F." pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="516 - 589" refId="ref10089" refString="Zhu, Y. - Q., Buck, W. R. &amp; Wang, Y. - F. (2010) A revision of Entodon (Entodontaceae) in East Asia. The Bryologist 113 (3): 516 - 589. https: // doi. org / 10.1639 / 0007 - 2745 - 113.3.516" type="journal article" year="2010">
Zhu 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7A2FF993FA35F06B" box="[1392,1452,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3326E8AFFF8C10F7FE2F9D5FC9EF124" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="234" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF8C10E7FE2F9D5FD13F1CB" blockId="8.[136,1452,1357,2088]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7FE2F9D5FD34F0D1" box="[189,685,1639,1666]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">
Comment:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7E11F9D5FD34F0D1" box="[334,685,1639,1665]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">Glossadelphus isopterygioides</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
was originally published as 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7B47F9D5FE8BF0F5" authority="Dixon (1915: 295)" authorityName="Dixon" authorityPageNumber="295" authorityYear="1915" class="Bryopsida" family="Sematophyllaceae" genus="Taxithelium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7B47F9D5FACFF0D1" box="[1048,1366,1639,1665]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Taxithelium isopterygioides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7A3AF9D5FE8BF0F5" author="Dixon, H. N." pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="1 - 295" refId="ref8193" refString="Dixon, H. N. (1915) Ceylonese mosses. Collected by the Rev. C. H. Binstead in 1913. Journal of Botany, British and Foreign 53: 1 - 295." type="journal article" year="1915">Dixon (1915: 295)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequently, it underwent a complex history of nomenclature changes. It was placed into 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7A13F938FA32F0F4" box="[1356,1451,1674,1700]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Entodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7A13F938FA32F0F4" box="[1356,1451,1674,1700]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Entodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7FF1F91FFED2F098" author="Dixon, H. N." box="[174,331,1709,1736]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref8271" refString="Dixon, H. N. (1933) Mosses of Hong Kong. With other Chinese mosses. Hong Kong Naturalist, Supplementum 2: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1933">Dixon (1933)</bibRefCitation>
, then to 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7EEBF91FFDA4F097" authorityName="M. Fleischer (1923:" authorityYear="1434" box="[436,573,1709,1735]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Taxiphyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7EEBF91FFDA4F097" box="[436,573,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Taxiphyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7D31F91FFC98F098" author="Buck, W. R." box="[622,769,1709,1736]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="519 - 527" refId="ref7946" refString="Buck, W. R. (1987) Notes on Asian Hypnaceae and associated taxa. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 45: 519 - 527." type="journal article" year="1987">Buck (1987)</bibRefCitation>
. Finally, it was placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7BB5F91FFD69F0BB" authority="(Hooker 1819: 155) Bosch &amp; Sande Lacoste" authorityName="Bosch &amp; Sande Lacoste" baseAuthorityName="Hooker" baseAuthorityPageNumber="155" baseAuthorityYear="1819" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Campylodontium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7BB5F91FFF62F0BB" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Campylodontium flavescens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7E56F963FE4EF0BB" author="Hooker, W. J." box="[265,471,1744,1771]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" refId="ref8650" refString="Hooker, W. J. (1819) Musci Exotici 2. 1818 - 1820. Longman et al., London, 155 pp." type="book" year="1819">Hooker 1819: 155</bibRefCitation>
) Bosch &amp; Sande Lacoste
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7C4CF963FB1DF0BB" author="Dozy, F. &amp; Molkenboer, J. H." box="[787,1156,1744,1771]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="1 - 238" refId="ref8332" refString="Dozy, F. &amp; Molkenboer, J. H. (1866) Bryologia Javanica 2. A. W. Sythoff, Leiden, pp. 1 - 238." type="book chapter" year="1866">Dozy &amp; Molkenboer (1866: 128)</bibRefCitation>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7BF3F963FADCF0BB" author="Tixier, P." box="[1196,1349,1745,1771]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="319 - 356" refId="ref9667" refString="Tixier, P. (1988) Le genre Glossadelphus Fleisch. (Sematophyllaceae, Musci) et sa valeur. Nova Hedwigia 46: 319 - 356." type="journal article" year="1988">Tixier (1988)</bibRefCitation>
. In 1980, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7FD7F946FE85F15E" authorityName="Bosch &amp; Sande Lacoste" baseAuthorityName="Hooker" baseAuthorityYear="1819" box="[136,284,1780,1806]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Campylodontium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7FD7F946FE85F15E" box="[136,284,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">C. flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7EAAF946FDE1F15E" authorityName="Hampe" authorityYear="1865" box="[501,632,1780,1806]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Mesonodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7EAAF946FDE1F15E" box="[501,632,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Mesonodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7DD8F947FD30F15E" box="[647,681,1781,1806]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">i.e.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7DEEF946FA85F15E" authority="(Hook.) W. R. Buck (1980: 117)" authorityName="W. R. Buck" authorityPageNumber="117" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Hook." box="[689,1308,1780,1807]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Mesonodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7DEEF946FC37F15E" box="[689,942,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Mesonodon flavescens</emphasis>
(Hook.) W.R. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7B0AF946FA85F15E" author="Buck, W. R." box="[1109,1308,1780,1806]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="71 - 159" refId="ref7918" refString="Buck, W. R. (1980) A generic revision of the Entodontaceae. Journal of the Hattori Botanical Laboratory 48: 71 - 159." type="journal article" year="1980">Buck (1980: 117)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, because the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7F8CF8A5FC87F161" authority="Dozy &amp; Molkenboer (1844: 301)" authorityName="Dozy &amp; Molkenboer" authorityPageNumber="301" authorityYear="1844" box="[211,798,1815,1842]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Campylodontium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7F8CF8A5FE0DF161" box="[211,404,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Campylodontium</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7EC1F8AAFC87F161" author="Dozy, F. &amp; Molkenboer, J. H." box="[414,798,1815,1842]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="1 - 309" refId="ref8301" refString="Dozy, F. &amp; Molkenboer, J. H. (1844) Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique, ser. 3, 2: 1 - 309." type="journal article" year="1844">Dozy &amp; Molkenboer (1844: 301)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed to discard (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF8C10E7B0EF8A5FB4DF161" author="Buck, W. R." box="[1105,1236,1815,1841]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" pagination="71 - 159" refId="ref7918" refString="Buck, W. R. (1980) A generic revision of the Entodontaceae. Journal of the Hattori Botanical Laboratory 48: 71 - 159." type="journal article" year="1980">Buck 1980</bibRefCitation>
). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7FD7F888FE15F104" authorityName="W. R. Buck" authorityYear="1980" baseAuthorityName="Hook." box="[136,396,1850,1876]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Mesonodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="flavescens">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7FD7F888FE15F104" box="[136,396,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Mesonodon flavescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has julaceous branches and plicate leaves, distinctly differing from 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7B8FF889FA3DF104" box="[1232,1444,1850,1877]" class="Bryopsida" family="Sematophyllaceae" genus="Taxithelium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7B8FF889FA3DF104" box="[1232,1444,1850,1877]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">G. isopterygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7FD7F8EFFE47F127" box="[136,478,1885,1911]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7FD7F8EFFE47F127" box="[136,478,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Glossadelphus isopterygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7D32F8EFFD6FF127" authorityName="M. Fleischer (1923:" authorityYear="1434" box="[621,758,1885,1911]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Taxiphyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7D32F8EFFD6FF127" box="[621,758,1885,1911]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Taxiphyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in foliose pseudoparaphyllia and complanate plant, but differs from the latter in more conspicuous alar cells.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF8C10E7FE2F816FE55FE78" blockId="8.[136,1452,1357,2088]" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7FE2F816FD8FF1EE" box="[189,534,1956,1982]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Glossadelphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7FE2F816FD8FF1EE" box="[189,534,1956,1982]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Glossadelphus isopterygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by (1) complanate plants, (2) oblong-ovate leaves with broadly acute apices, strongly constricted at the bases, (3) ecostate, (4) serrate upper leaf margins, (5) prominent alar regions with numerous large, hyaline rectangle cells, and (6) elongate and smooth laminal cells. These features well match with the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF8C10E7E39F7BFFE5CFE77" box="[358,453,2061,2087]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Entodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="8" pageNumber="233" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF8C10E7E39F7BFFE5CFE77" box="[358,453,2061,2087]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="233">Entodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF576D89FFF9C10F7FD7F9ABFEC0F027" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392598" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6392598" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392598/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" startId="9.[136,229,1561,1583]" targetBox="[171,1408,219,1524]" targetPageId="9">
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF9C10F7FD7F9ABFEC0F027" blockId="9.[136,1451,1561,1655]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7FD7F9ABFF66F07E" bold="true" box="[136,255,1561,1583]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7E5AF9ABFE23F07E" authorityName="Brotherus" authorityYear="1923" box="[261,442,1561,1582]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Entodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="obtusatus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7E5AF9ABFE23F07E" box="[261,442,1561,1582]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">Entodon obtusatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A: Plants; B: Branch; C: Branch leaves; D, G: Pseudoparaphyllia and primordia; E–F: Base of laminal cells; H: Median laminal cells; I–J: Leaf apex. All from holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7C4AF98FFB86F002" box="[789,1055,1597,1618]" class="Bryopsida" family="Sematophyllaceae" genus="Taxithelium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7C4AF98FFB86F002" box="[789,1055,1597,1618]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">Taxithelium isopterygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Scale bars: a for B; b for C; c for E–F; d for D, G, I–J; e for H.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFF9C10F7FE2F914FC9EF124" blockId="9.[136,1452,1702,1908]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF9C10F7FE2F914FE78F090" author="Ochyra, R. &amp; Ireland, R. R." box="[189,481,1702,1728]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" pagination="485 - 489" refId="ref9219" refString="Ochyra, R. &amp; Ireland, R. R. (2009) A new species of Taxiphyllum (Musci: Hypnaceae) from Sri Lanka. Novon 19: 485 - 489. https: // doi. org / 10.3417 / 2009012" type="journal article" year="2009">
Ochyra and 
<collectingCountry id="F33F7D91FFF9C10F7E1DF914FE08F090" box="[322,401,1702,1728]" name="Ireland" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">Ireland</collectingCountry>
(2009)
</bibRefCitation>
confirmed 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7D02F914FC09F090" box="[605,912,1702,1728]" class="Bryopsida" family="Sematophyllaceae" genus="Taxithelium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7D02F914FC09F090" box="[605,912,1702,1728]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">Taxithelium isopterygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’s status in 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7B59F914FBFCF090" box="[1030,1125,1702,1728]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Entodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7B59F914FBFCF090" box="[1030,1125,1702,1728]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">Entodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7BD9F915FED4F0B4" authority="(Dixon) Dixon (1933: 27)" authorityName="Dixon" authorityPageNumber="27" authorityYear="1933" baseAuthorityName="Dixon" class="Bryopsida" family="Sematophyllaceae" genus="Taxithelium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7BD9F915FAD7F090" box="[1158,1358,1702,1728]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">E. isopterygioides</emphasis>
(Dixon) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF9C10F7FD7F978FED4F0B4" author="Dixon, H. N." box="[136,333,1738,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref8271" refString="Dixon, H. N. (1933) Mosses of Hong Kong. With other Chinese mosses. Hong Kong Naturalist, Supplementum 2: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1933">Dixon (1933: 27)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and pointed out a mistake in Index Muscorum (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF9C10F7C33F978FBBDF0B5" author="Wijk, R. Van Der &amp; Margadant, W. D. &amp; Florschutz, P. A." box="[876,1060,1738,1765]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" pagination="206 - 217" refId="ref9857" refString="Wijk, R. Van Der, Margadant, W. D. &amp; Florschutz, P. A. (1962) Entodon. Index Muscorum 2: 206 - 217." type="journal article" year="1962">
Wijk 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7CF3F979FC7DF0B4" box="[940,996,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">et al.</emphasis>
1962
</bibRefCitation>
) of treating 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7BF0F979FAE0F0B4" authorityName="Dixon" authorityYear="1933" baseAuthorityName="Dixon" box="[1199,1401,1738,1764]" class="Bryopsida" family="Sematophyllaceae" genus="Taxithelium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7BF0F979FAE0F0B4" box="[1199,1401,1738,1764]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">E. isopterygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a nomen nudum. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFF9C10F7E66F95CFE63F158" author="Zhu, Y. - Q. &amp; Buck, W. R. &amp; Wang, Y. - F." box="[313,506,1774,1800]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" pagination="516 - 589" refId="ref10089" refString="Zhu, Y. - Q., Buck, W. R. &amp; Wang, Y. - F. (2010) A revision of Entodon (Entodontaceae) in East Asia. The Bryologist 113 (3): 516 - 589. https: // doi. org / 10.1639 / 0007 - 2745 - 113.3.516" type="journal article" year="2010">
Zhu 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7E31F95DFE3EF158" box="[366,423,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7D0CF95DFC87F158" authorityName="Dixon" authorityYear="1933" baseAuthorityName="Dixon" box="[595,798,1774,1800]" class="Bryopsida" family="Sematophyllaceae" genus="Taxithelium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7D0CF95DFC87F158" box="[595,798,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">E. isopterygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7CA5F95DFB1CF158" authorityName="Brotherus" authorityYear="1923" box="[1018,1157,1774,1800]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Entodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="obtusatus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7CA5F95DFB1CF158" box="[1018,1157,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">E. obtusatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a nomen nudum. After careful examination of literatures and 
<typeStatus id="549383A3FFF9C10F7D73F8A0FDC5F17C" box="[556,604,1810,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">type</typeStatus>
materials, we recognized 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7C22F8A1FBDCF17C" authorityName="Dixon" authorityYear="1933" baseAuthorityName="Dixon" box="[893,1093,1810,1836]" class="Bryopsida" family="Sematophyllaceae" genus="Taxithelium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="isopterygioides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7C22F8A1FBDCF17C" box="[893,1093,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">E. isopterygioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a validly published name and a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7E7AF885FE37F100" authorityName="Brotherus" authorityYear="1923" box="[293,430,1846,1872]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Entodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="obtusatus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7E7AF885FE37F100" box="[293,430,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">E. obtusatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7EE4F884FD12F100" authorityName="Brotherus" authorityYear="1923" box="[443,651,1846,1872]" class="Bryopsida" family="Entodontaceae" genus="Entodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="9" pageNumber="234" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="obtusatus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7EE4F884FD12F100" box="[443,651,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">Entodon obtusatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other Chinese 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFF9C10F7C80F884FB0CF100" box="[991,1173,1846,1872]" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFF9C10F7C80F884FBA7F100" box="[991,1086,1846,1872]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="234">Entodon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
in its rather small plants, dimorphic leaves, and lingulate and obtuse dorsal leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
